<!-- ============== 25 PATTERNS ============== -->
<section class="section" id="patterns">
  <div class="kicker">Shared · 25</div>
  <div class="page-head"><h2 style="margin:0">Patterns &amp; states</h2><span class="route">cross-cutting</span></div>

  <h4>Empty states</h4>
  <p>Centered: a quiet line-icon, a plain title, one sentence of direction, and a single primary action. Never an apology, never decorative. "No orders yet — your purchase orders will appear here once buyers place them."</p>

  <h4>Loading</h4>
  <p>Tables and ledgers use <strong>skeleton rows</strong> with the real column rhythm (hairlines visible) so the layout doesn't jump. Metric tiles shimmer the number block only. No full-page spinners on navigation.</p>

  <h4>Errors</h4>
  <p>Inline, at the field or row that failed, in danger color with a plain fix instruction ("GSTIN must be 15 characters"). System-level failures use a dismissible banner that states what happened and the retry action — in the interface's voice, not an apology.</p>

  <h4>Responsive collapse of tables</h4>
  <p>Below tablet, each ledger row becomes a stacked record card: the primary identifier and status on top, secondary fields as label→value pairs, money kept mono and right-of-label. The action set moves into a row overflow menu.</p>

  <h4>Accessibility floor (non-negotiable)</h4>
  <ul class="clean">
    <li>Status is never color-only — every badge carries a text label and a shape-distinct dot.</li>
    <li>Visible 2px evergreen focus ring on every interactive element; full keyboard paths through drawers and modals (focus trap + Esc to close).</li>
    <li>Body text meets WCAG AA on paper; the evergreen primary meets AA for button text.</li>
